JOHANNESBURG - Sandile Mantsoe's bail application has been postponed to 30 August. Mantsoe’s accused of killing his ex-girlfriend, Karabo Mokoena. The 27-year-old is also facing charges of defeating the ends of justice. READ: Mantsoe confessed to murdering Mokoena to sever blood-tie: NPA Mantsoe denies killing Mokoena, suggesting she may have committed suicide. But the state says he confessed to a police officer. It's believed it may have been a ritual killing, with Mantsoe trying to save his business. Mokoena's charred remains were found in Lyndhurst, Johannesburg, in April. eNCA